{
  "text": "3. The multiple-stage FDR procedure based penalty. In sparse problems where the number of nonzero coefficients is small relative to the searched pool, the factor of m 0 /m is close to 1 and not that important. In nonsparse problems, adaptive FDR controlling methods were offered that have better performance as testing procedures [CITATION_1] , [CITATION_2] , [CITATION_3] and many others]. They should have potentially better performance as model selection procedures. Unfortunately, not all such procedures can be translated into penalty functions and thereby be used in a simple way as model selection methods.",
